            "JHU EP explains AI’s new role in healthcare, where it’s expected to go, and how a master’s degree can help you advance your current healthcare career. From diagnostic tools to organizational optimization, AI is shaping the way clinicians deliver care and patients receive it. Moreover, 85% of healthcare leaders are adopting generative AI at scale to streamline clinical productivity and patient engagement. AI systems rely heavily on large volumes of patient data to learn and make decisions, often drawing from electronic health records, genetic information, and even real-time data from wearable devices. * Healthcare Machine Learning Engineer: Designs and deploys AI models tailored to clinical environments and patient needs. * Medical Informatics Specialist: Bridges gaps between healthcare IT systems and clinical practice, often managing data integration for AI tools. Collaboration among technology, medicine, ethics, and public policy professionals is needed to create clinically effective, ethical, and scalable AI solutions for healthcare.",
